Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @Rigatoni Pasta{180%grams} to the water and bring back to
the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the saucepan. Drizzle with
@oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds.
Chop into 1cm chunks.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain the @Mozzarella{1%ball} and squeeze out as much liquid as you can. Pat dry
with #kitchen paper{}, then tear into small pieces.

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%grams}. Preheat the #grill{} to high.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%grams} and
pepper chunks. Stir-fry until tender, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Lower the heat to medium and add the garlic and @Roasted Spice and Herb Blend{1%sachet}.
Cook for ~{30%seconds} more.

Stir in the @Tomato Puree{30%grams}, @Red Wine Stock Paste{28%grams},
@Creme Fraiche{75%grams}, @Honey{1%tbsp} and @Water for the Sauce{150%milliliters}.

> See pantry for both water and honey amounts.

Bring the sauce to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{3-4%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and @pepper{} if needed.

> IMPORTANT: Cook so there's no pink in the middle of the chicken.

Add the @Baby Spinach{40%grams} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and
piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

When ready, combine the cooked pasta and sauce (in whichever pan is biggest).
Stir through the @Harissa Paste{50%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder).
Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick, then transfer to an
appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}.

Scatter over the mozzarella and Cheddar.

Pop the dish under the grill and cook until the cheese is bubbling and golden,
~{4-5%minutes}.

When ready, share the harissa pasta bake between your #bowls{}.

Enjoy!